IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: TO PROMOTE RESPONSIBLE AND EFFECTIVE POLITICAL AND COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT BY BUSINESSES.
IRS990.MissionDescription: TO PROMOTE RESPONSIBLE AND EFFECTIVE POLITICAL AND COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT BY BUSINESSES AND THEIR EMPLOYEES.
IRS990.Description: COMMUNICATIONS: THE COUNCIL'S PROFESSIONAL STAFF PROVIDES RESOURCES VIA THEIR WEBSITE, WEEKLY BLOG, AND MONTHLY NEWSLETTER TO KEEP MEMBERS ABREAST OF BEST PRACTICES IN THE FIELD OF PUBLIC AFFAIRS.

Activity2.Description: PUBLICATIONS: IN CONJUCTION WITH THE FOUNDATION FOR PUBLIC AFFAIRS, THE COUNCIL PRODUCES NUMEROUS HIGH-IMPACT PUBLICATIONS ANNUALLY. MEMBERS OF THE COUNCIL RECEIVE A COMPLIMENTARY SUBSCRIPTION TO "IMPACT", THE COUNCIL'S NEWSLETTER.

Activity3.Description: WORKSHOP: THE COUNCIL SPONSORS CONFERENCES ON A VARIETY OF TOPICS GEARED TO IMPROVING THE PROFFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT OF PUBLIC AFFAIRS PROFESSIONALS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION HAS MEMBERS THAT RECEIVE BENEFITS DURING THE YEAR IN EXCHANGE FOR MEMBERSHIP DUES.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE 990 IS PREPARED BY OUR INDEPENDENT AUDITING FIRM. THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE REVIEWS THE 990 ALONG WITH THE PRESIDENT PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS. MEMBERS OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ARE PROVIDED WITH A COPY OF THE 990 PRIOR TO FILING.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION MONITORS COMPLIANCE WITH CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUALLY. AT THE ANNUAL BOARD MEETING, BOARD MEMBERS ARE GIVEN COPIES OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. THEY ARE ASKED TO RESPOND IN WRITING TO ANY POSSIBLE CONFLICTS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A COMPENSATION STUDY WAS DONE BY AN INDEPENDENT CONSULTING FIRM. SALARY RANGE WAS DETERMINED FOR ALL STAFF INCLUDING THE PRESIDENT AND OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE AGREED ON SALARY AND COMPENSATION FOR THE PRESIDENT.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THESE DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION UPON VERBAL OR WRITTEN REQUEST.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: CHANGES IN NET ASSETS OR FUND BALANCES:

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: PROCESS FOR ASSUMING RESPONSIBILITY OF AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT HAS NOT CHANGED FROM PREVIOUS YEAR.
